When I was a kid, I had this urge to create art and follow this path. So, on my mind there was a God of Art who was lighting the way for me. I still believe on this

The Kiss, Gustav Klimt

When I was a kid, I thought 'The Kiss' by Gustav Klimt on our wall was a portrait of my parents because I didn't know art. I saw it as a beautiful sign of family unity. I thought it was a portrait of them until my teens, when I discovered it was a world-famous masterwork

No 😂 , it was actually a remix of a Klimt's piece done by a Brazilian artist. But on my kid's mind, I had 100% sure the painting was about my parents, this connected me a lot to art. After a lot of years, I saw the original Klimt's piece on the internet and I catch it was a masterpiece
Sorry if my post sounds like they had an original Klimt's piece. English is actually my second language

I don’t think we’ll ever see something like HEN, specially because we were all learning together back in the day. Nowadays we already knows a lot about blockchain and minting process, so we don’t have that magical feeling from the unknown +

Also, the UI and UX experience on HEN was so different, because it was so simplified it reminded me of early internet websites. The discovery experience was stunning, how you could meet new artists on the feed and specially about hDAO and low fee was an entry point for so many artists outside the north-global space +

There’s a lot of reason for me to set high standards visions for HEN, maybe because the Brazilian community saw it as our own home in the CryptoArt space

But I’m having a lot of fun vibing and making new connections here on /cryptoart
